### Default Primary Application ID in Serverless Mode

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This configuration change ensures that `primary_application_id` defaults to 'Unknown' in serverless mode for the New Relic Node.js agent. This allows Distributed Tracing to function correctly even when `NEW_RELIC_PRIMARY_APPLICATION_ID` is not explicitly defined.

```javascript
{
  // ...
  primary_application_id: 'Unknown' // Defaults in serverless mode
  // ...
}
```

