### Node.js Datastore Segment Descriptors rowCallback Property

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet highlights the addition of the `rowCallback` property to datastore segment descriptors in the Node.js agent. This allows the shim to record a given function/parameter as a per-row callback, which can be called multiple times and counted for traces.

```javascript
// Assume 'newrelic' is required and configured
// This relates to internal agent instrumentation, not direct user code.

// When the agent instruments a datastore operation that involves processing rows,
// it might use a descriptor like this:

/*
  const segmentDescriptor = {
    ... other properties ...
    rowCallback: function(row) {
      // Process each row
      console.log('Processing row:', row);
    }
  };
  shim.recordSubSegment(segmentDescriptor);
*/

// The 'rowCallback' function provided here will be executed for each row processed.
// The agent will count how many times this callback is invoked, contributing to trace data.
```

