### Instrument gRPC Client Calls in Node.js Agent

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This change adds instrumentation for gRPC client calls within the Node.js agent. It covers unary, streaming, and bidirectional calls, enabling New Relic to trace these interactions. This provides visibility into the performance and behavior of gRPC services used by your application.

```javascript
// Example of instrumented gRPC client call (conceptual):
const grpc = require('@grpc/grpc-js');
const client = new MyServiceClient('localhost:50051', grpc.credentials.createInsecure());

// The New Relic agent will automatically instrument calls made through this client.
```

