### Add Custom Parameters to Transaction Traces (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

Introduces the `.addCustomParameter(name, value)` API call for adding custom data to transaction traces. It also extends `.noticeError(error, customParameters)` to include additional parameters for error traces. This functionality is part of the Node.js New Relic agent.

```javascript
newrelic.addCustomParameter(name, value);
newrelic.noticeError(error, customParameters);
```

