### Bind Promise Calls in Node.js Shim

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet shows the usage of `bindPromise()` on the `Shim` prototype in the New Relic Node.js agent. This method is used by instrumentation to correctly handle promise-based asynchronous operations, ensuring proper tracing and error handling.

```javascript
// This is typically used internally by the New Relic agent instrumentation.
// Example of how it might be conceptually used:
// Shim.prototype.bindPromise = function(promise) {
//   // ... internal logic to wrap and instrument the promise ...
//   return instrumentedPromise;
// };
```

