### Replace addCustomParameter with addCustomAttribute

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/Migration Guide.md

The `newrelic.addCustomParameter()` method for adding single custom parameters is deprecated. It is replaced by `newrelic.addCustomAttribute()`, which provides a more consistent naming convention for custom trace attributes.

```javascript
/**
 * Deprecated method: newrelic.addCustomParameter()
 */
// Example of old usage (deprecated):
// newrelic.addCustomParameter('userId', 'user123');

/**
 * New method: newrelic.addCustomAttribute()
 */
// Example of new usage:
newrelic.addCustomAttribute('userId', 'user123');

```

